FBIS3-15076 "drsov041_a_94021" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Diplomat Gives Yeltsin Message to 'Arafat LD0203092094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 2 Mar 94 LD0203092094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Russian president's special representative Igor Ivanov has had a meeting in Tunis with the Palestinian leader Yasir 'Arafat. He handed him a personal message from Boris Yeltsin. The message expresses Russia's firm intention to further the achievement of peace in the Middle East. After the talks were concluded, the Russian diplomat set off for Israel. Igor Ivanov spoke of Russia's support for the Palestinian proposal to ensure an international presence in the territories occupied by Israel.
